his page works best with JavaScript. Disabling it will result in some disabled or missing features. You can still see all customer reviews for the product.
his remote control updates your obsolete Tivo box (with a download of the new "experience" software that changes the layout of clickables on your TV screen) -- into a voice controller.
It "pairs" itself with the Tivo Bolt -- you have to work a little harder for older models - and it comes with the newest Tivo model.
HOWEVER - and this is no fault of TiVo\'s so no stars off for this Remote - getting the "codes" into the remote to make it control older (7 years +) TV\'s may be harder, especially if you want this remote to Control a separate (optical cable connected) Home Theater sound system that is 3 or 4 years old.
iVo has done a wondrous thing, here -- massive addition of value to a ridiculously over-priced item you have connected to a "lifetime service" account at TiVo which juggles and sorts TV programs from Cable, Netflix, Amazon, Hulu, etc.
It does not provide all the functions of all the equipment you might have connected to your TV, and has the usual long list of possible "codes" that would enable various models of various brands of equipment.  Very tedious going through the list.  I found oldest models listed first, which helped.
But TiVo has made a great start with voice-control retrofitting.  I love my TiVo Bolt and Mini that makes other TVs work with the TiVo data sorting.  To understand what a TiVo "is" and what it can do for those heading toward dropping Cable and OTA antenna, you just have to find someone who has it and will let you play with it.  The Bolt model is fantastic.  The business philosophy demonstrated by this upgrade of older equipment is a "wave of the future" -- and very refreshing.  I just love this thing.  Voice control may not be your priority now, but it may easily become so.
IVO VOX remote works great with my TIVO Bolt, but would not RF pair to a Mini without a dongle for the Mini that is not included unless you buy the remote directly from TIVO. Without this pairing the Voice button will not work with the new TIVO Experience and you only have an IR based remote.
