ivo Has Nailed Voice Control -- Worth the Wait
"Tivo made us wait quite a long time to get a voice-controlled remote, but they have really nailed it. I paired this with my existing Tivo Bolt -- took just a minute and was easy to do, although I did have to use the advanced pairing since it didn't automatically connect. I was surprised that the bluetooth connection actually works better than my old RF Tivo remote -- much faster and more responsive when you hit a button. Wow. Even better, I have my TiVo in a closed closet and the Bluetooth seems to connect more reliably RF."
hen there is the voice control. First, make sure you have the new TiVo update, which you can request directly at Tivo.com (although I\'m sure it will be automatically downloaded to all customers soon). It understands my voice extremely well, even with noise in the room. You can ask for things like a tv station "NBC" and it will take you directly there. Ask it for a game like "Michigan Football" and presto, you get the next upcoming game with the option to record. Or ask it for a show you have recorded, and it also pops up to start watching. For the most part, it understands everything you ask it, but when I asked for "60 Minutes" it couldn\'t help. Not sure why, but I\'m sure they\'ll keep refining it.
"Finally, I like the new Tivo interface, but it has a few quirks. First, they took away my favorite version of the TiVo guide -- not sure why. I guess now with the voice remote, it won't matter much. It also seems to show recorded episodes with the oldest showing first -- I prefer the opposite. Overall, it's gotten a little overwhelming and confusing, but perhaps will get better once I use it more."
\n  Was this review helpful to you?
